From Perry Reed Subject Re How Redirect PRINT MANAGER To FILE hpcc comp os ms windows misc By SWH am Apr , Hello, Who can tell me Where can I find the PD or ShareWare Which can CAPTURE windows 's output of printer mananger I want to capture the output of HP Laser Jet III Though the PostScript can setup to print to file,but HP can't I try DOS's redirect program,but they can't work in Windows Thankx for any help You CAN print to a file from an HP or any other printer Just go into the Printers section of your Control Panel Select the printer you want to re direct to a file, and click on Connect Then choose FILE as the port to connect the printer to When you print from any application to that printer, Windows will prompt you for a file name for the file into which you want to capture the printout It's pretty easy Good luck ' ' Perry Reed ' ' ' ' Be young, be foolish, be lucky in love ' ' '